This place are cool for relaxing and doing work", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Azim", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "There's free WiFi and a lot of seating.

People always talk about ambiance when they go to cafés and coffee shops, "cosy and quiet" they'd say. But just because a place isn't quiet doesn't mean it isn't cosy.

This Burger King is placed beside a hustling traffic light intersection in town, neighbouring two big tyre workshops. Sounds bad? No, not at all. It's distanced quite away from it all so the noise isn't really overpowering, in fact, it's relaxing and cosy.

Here as you relax at the outside tables after eating your lunch, you'll hear the familiar sounds of metropolitan traffic along with impact wrenches dealing with the lug nuts of car wheels, both drowning out the low-volume radio broadcast.

All this while the "natural" wind breeze cools you down.

So far, this is the best place for a relaxing unique city ambiance in Batu Pahat. You can read, you can chat, you can just take a break and have a short nap. {"name": "Woodfire Eco Spring", "phone": "019-735 3565", "lat": 1.58839, "lng": 103.7613037, "review": [{"r_name": "Keryn Lee", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Went during late evening and despite the quiet timing before the dinner hours, the waiting time for the food still required at least 30 minutes to be served. Ordered their Nashville Hot Chicken Platter and the items were pleasant - The chicken was juicy and coated with crispy layer. I specifically requested for my order to be extra spicy and it hit the right amount of kick.

Personally the portion could be improved by having more chicken/breads but I did appreciated the extra portion of the dip that came with the meal. The dip went well with both the chicken and the bread. On another note, I would highly recommend their milkshakes! Tried their Oreo Milkshake and it was delightful.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "kaiser misaki", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Located in Eco Spring, and decided to try this restaurant after having cakes at a nearby cafe. The restaurant only opens at 3pm on a Friday. So I guess this would be a very late lunch.

The burgers are really good. Super tasty and the portions are huge. I almost couldn't finish it. Buns were soft, although it was a bit oily. I ordered the beef brisket burger and it was really an explosion of flavours and textures. Really quite a good burger. My friend ordered some chicken platter but it was really spicy. If you like spicy food this is the one to order. The fries were very good. Crispy.

Was crowded at 3pm when it opened. And the restaurant quickly filled up. This eco spring area is posh but yet still cant fix the flies issue like the rest of Malaysia, even in this air-conditioned premise.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Kenny Yap", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Came on a weekday around 1240pm and the restaurant was half full. I was alone so I just wanted a beef burger to try and a side of brisket. Turns out, the staff went to key in a beef burger and a brisket burger. I only realized after paying and sat down. I immediately went back to ask if I could cancel the brisket burger order. Without hesitating, she said that the kitchen had already processed the order and started cooking. That was odd as there were people infront of me waiting for their order. She also blamed me for saying I said yes to the brisket burger when I didn’t recall her asking. I just said I want the brisket (which is an item on the menu), but it was her word vs mine and I already paid so I didn’t want to argue. After some persuasion, I managed to change one of the beef patty to a chicken patty (both were same price). The chicken patty however wasn’t crispy, and felt rather soggy w all the sauce on top.

I ended up having to force myself to eat 2 burgers. The portions are huge and very hard to take in one single bite. The fried onions and the lettuce didn’t feel crisp and fresh. While the ingredients were tasty, it didn’t feel premium. The brisket which I spent so much money ordering turned out to be very normal only, quite tough instead of the break apart easily I had imagined. Overall, it wasn’t a pleasant experience", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "wrinklefreebrain", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Really loved the food, staff were very nice too!

Chicken breaded Burger is so huge, the batter is a bit pepper-ish but chicken is juicy and tender. Smoked Burger are good too!

The other type of burger taste as per usual roadside burger.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Aditya Choudhary", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "While digital has become the marketing strategy of choice for businesses today, this does not mean that word of mouth is obsolete. Word of mouth still remains a powerful tool for marketing a business, and with the interconnected network of digital channels at our fingertips, it’s easier than ever for customers to tell others about their best (and worst) experiences. Online reviews are today’s word of mouth marketing, and they can make or break your business. Why Are Online Reviews so Important?

Crowd-sourced online review sites like Yelp, Google Maps, and TripAdvisor (among others) play a crucial role in determining the success of businesses. Your potential, current, and loyal customers are using them daily to make their decisions. Why?

Accessibility

Online reviews have also become incredibly easy to find, thanks to search engines, mobile apps, and the addition of review features onto popular platforms like Facebook.

Visibility

In many cases, reviews for a business become visible to consumers before they even click a link. For example, a regular Google search for “bathroom remodeling” yields the following local results. As you can see, the ratings for each business are included in the results:

Sometimes results will even include a snippet from a customer review. Once again, this is before you even click on a result.

How Online Reviews Help Your Business

Making positive information about your business available online isn’t the only benefit of reviews. Read on to learn more ways that reviews can help in your marketing efforts.", "r_ts": ""}], "operation_time": "6–11 pm", "operation_day": "Closed on Sunday", "state": "Johor", "city": "Johor Bahru", "landmark": "", "creator_name": "Faizul", "waze_url": "https://waze.com/ul?ll=1.5018219,103.7431053&z=10"}

Would recommend their briyani kambing.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "sonjaya Indonesia", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Best nasi beriani and nasi ayam in malaysia also you can order group with special room", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Phoora Safuraa", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Their specialities is chicken rice and its very popular among the local..but their biryani is also worth to try..", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "N.a.d S", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "A favourite of my family (maybe it reminds my dad of the good old days?), hence, I had high expectation which did not exceed.

Expect a queue over lunch time, we were fortunate to arrive before noon and the crowd started rushing in. I was uncomfortable inside the restaurant. It's air-conditioned to make the experience better but it was so stuffy as the air from the kitchen opens up to the eating area. The gap between the tables were small to maximize space, I guess that's how business is. Barely any space to walk.

Menu was simple - few types of nasi ayam. Taste-wise pretty average, I've heard it used to be better. My notion is - I guess for some people it was something they grew up with, the excitement of going to town and eating Baser Chicken Rice.
• Nasi ayam - I find it dry instead of juicy. The soup in particular was good, I can taste a hint of sesame oil which makes the soup nicer.
• Nasi ayam berlada - I love spicy food but for this, I'm not a big fan of the chili, there wasn't much taste to it except that it was spicy. Harapkan pedas aje.
• Sayur campur - I can say it deserves a thumbs up and was cooked in chinese style, simple with garlic and oyster sauce. I would recommend this as a side dish for the chicken rice as the chicken rice salad portion was small.

Service was fast despite the busy restaurant during lunch hour. Price-wise is reasonable, we paid RM90.70 for a family of 7, with extra chicken & veggies.

I would recommend to go here at least once to discover what the hype is all about but for me, there are plenty of other delicious places to eat in and around Kota Tinggi.", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "Khalida A", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "One of the famous spots for lunch in Kota Tinggi. The first time I came here, I did not impress with the food. I felt like it was just an average Chicken Rice. But yesterday, we had lunch here. The Chicken Rice was somehow tasted different from my previous visit. It was more tasty, more flavorful. The Kerabu Mangga was excellent. Fast service.", "r_ts": ""}], "operation_time": "10 am–6:30 pm", "operation_day": "Everyday", "state": "Johor", "city": "Kota Tinggi", "landmark": "", "creator_name": "Faizul", "waze_url": "https://waze.com/ul?ll=1.7279067,103.8982408&z=10"}

The lasagna is nice. We even tapau one to enjoy at home :)", "r_ts": ""}, {"r_name": "des leo", "id": "", "r_item": "-", "r_review": "Okay so I was very excited to try this lamb and was really having positive vibes about the place. However much to be said so let me break it down:
Total stars 2.51 and here's the reason:

Service: 3.8 stars this was good service the waiter greeted with a smile and was polite. Didn't offer much advice but that's okay.

Food: 3.25 stars only :( very disappointing because the stars were the salad and the soup!
Salad: standard and average mixed salad I liked the sesame dressing 2.5stars
Steak fries: 4 stars really good fries!
Mushrooms soup: 3 stars nice standard and average though so not much to say here
Lamb: plate was cold and sadly the lamb was chewy and not well handled so it was not cooked evenly. They didnt respect the meat 2 stars
Beef Burger: came 50 mins late and was cold!
1 star

Prep Time: 0.5stars :(
Horribly slow! My goodness there were 2 tables the kitchen was prepping for. Ours was 3 pax and another was a a big group of 8pax. They more than halfway thru already serving the 8 pax before starting our order but it took 35 mins which wasn't a problem but there were 4 people in the kitchen and the slowest item on our menu was 50mins late the burger?! When the burger arrived they were apologetic and gave usb2 mushroom soups. Very nice of the manager but I was wondering if I didnt say anything about the burger woild he have even bothered? If it was genuine the soup would have been served to apologize for the delay. But anyway I thought they were really nice people. No faulting them on the attitude but I think the kitchen process is weak and not well controlled.

So overall great nice people with average sides and a poor main course and really slow kitchen process.

Total bill: rm150 at the end of the meal we didn't feel satisfied. If it was a hot meal that hit the spot the 150 would be worth it.

Will i come back - maybe....won't be coming back soon but I hope they improve because I will try again in 6 months to see if they improve as I want to support local businesses.
